{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Notably, negative words hold a significant role in shaping the semantic context of the input text.Therefore, this article introduces a quantum-like tensor compression sentence representation, rooted in constraint functions, with the aim of accentuating the semantic influence originating from local details like semantic and grammatical correlations among words within input sentences.",
    "This approach seeks to comprehensively address the semantic repercussions stemming from contextual nuances within input sentences.",
    "The framework of the provided method to compute sentence similarity is shown in Fig. 1.First, the neighboring words in the target text are correlated to enhance the semantic impact of the local contextual information provided by the words composing the target text.",
    "Taking into account that various part-of-speech (PoS) combinations can illustrate some common modifications among words [39,40], the proposed method enhances the semantic influence of the negative word in a sentence via the correlation of two adjacent words.",
    "This process serves to accentuate the negative semantics of the sentence.Second, the current density matrix [43], which is originally based on independent words, is expanded to include the mixed-state projection operator involving two adjacent words."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
